2.20	Saikei	Saikei	Saikei ) literally translates as "planted landscape". It is the art of creating tray landscapes that combine miniature living trees with soil, rocks, water, and related vegetation (like ground cover) in a single tray or similar container. A saikei landscape will remind the viewer of a natural location through its overall topography, choice of ground materials, and the species used in its plantings.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Penjing_img_2257.jpg/320px-Penjing_img_2257.jpg
